com.inqwell.any.decimal

Interface DecimalNumber


  • public interface DecimalNumber
    Support alternative implementations of fixed scale decimal numbers. This interface exists solely to allow alternative implementations of objects representing BigDecimals. The (non-functionally extending) derivation of java.math.BigDecimal implements this interface, as does the Inq representation of null for this type.

    The crux of the problem is that the scale of an AnyDecimal is held within the underlying BigDecimal, yet we don't want to lose this information in the null representation since it is maintained when an assignment (via setValue) is made.
